http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 24 Dec 2020
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2020; 33(52) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=37261


Highly pathogenic influenza A viruses (infection with) (non-poultry including wild birds), Japan
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 24 Dec 2020 from Dr. Norio Kumagai, Director, Chief Veterinary Officer, Animal Health Division, Food Safety and Consumer Affairs Bureau, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo, Japan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 3 Dec 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 9 Dec 2020
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 25 Mar 2018
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Highly pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H5N8
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic), laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (4)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 4

Outbreak 1: Wakayama-City 1, Wakayama
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Dec 2020
Outbreak status: resolved 3 Dec 2020
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Mandarin Dux: _Aix galericulata_ (Anatidae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A dead _Aix galericulata_ was found and tested.

Outbreak 2: Yakage-Town 1, Okayama
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Dec 2020
Outbreak status: resolved 4 Dec 2020
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Peregrin falcon: _Falco peregrinus_ (Falconidae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A dead _Falco peregrinus_ was found and tested.

Outbreak 3: Mitoyo-City 1, Kagawa
Date of start of the outbreak: 8 Dec 2020
Outbreak status: resolved 8 Dec 2020
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Eastern buzzard: _Buteo japonicus_ (Accipitridae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A dead _Buteo japonicus_ was found and tested

Outbreak 4: Izumi-City 1, Kagoshima
Date of start of the outbreak: 18 Dec 2020
Outbreak status: resolved 18 Dec 2020
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Hooded crane: _Grus monachal_ (Gruidae) / - / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: A dead _Grus monachal_ was found and tested

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Contact with wild species.

Epidemiological comments: Cases in wild birds: Wakayama-City 1; A dead _Aix galericulata_ (Mandarin Duck) was collected on [3 Dec 2020] and tested against avian influenza virus. The Tottori University conducted RT-PCR and gene sequencing tests and confirmed that the subtype of the virus was H5N8. Yakage-Town 1; a dead _Falco peregrinus_ (Peregrine Falcon) was collected on [4 Dec 2020] and tested against avian influenza virus. The Tottori University conducted RT-PCR and gene sequencing tests and confirmed that the subtype of the virus was H5N8. Mitoyo-City 1; a dead _Buteo japonicus_ (Eastern buzzard) was collected on [8 Dec 2020] and tested against avian influenza virus. The Tottori University conducted RT-PCR and gene sequencing tests and confirmed that the subtype of the virus was H5N8. Izumi-City 1; a dead _Grus monachal_ (Hooded crane) was collected on [18 Dec 2020] and tested against avian influenza virus. The Kagoshima University conducted RT-PCR and gene sequencing tests and confirmed that the subtype of the virus was H5N8. Enhanced monitoring of wild birds is ongoing within a 10km [approx. 0.6mi] radius around the sites.

Control measures
Measures applied: surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; vaccination prohibited; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
