[Wild birds can normally carry AI viruses in their respiratory or intestinal tracts but they do not commonly get sick, which allow them to carry the viruses on long distances along their migration flyways.

An update on recent outbreaks of Avian Influenza H5/H7 in the East Asia region was presented in the GFTADs Regional Workshop for diseases of poultry in Asia and the Pacific Region on 2 Dec 2020. The presentation can be seen at
https://rr-asia.oie.int/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/h5-h7-eastasia-sakoda.pdf. - Mod.CRD

